  "text": "coordinates can be restricted to an arbitrary space (like a cylinder) or additional energy may be assigned to arbitrary faces, to mimic effects of differential surface tension around adhering blastomeres for instance [CITATION_1] . We provide several input files in the folder DPP package\\DPP files\\generating_shapes_from_SE\\generic shapes\\, which can be used to create 1-cell spheres, rods, typical 2-cell, 4-cell or 8-cell stage embryos. In the DPP package, we further provide more detailed guidelines to create other shapes and constrains with SE. For the method description below we will use the example file \"4 cells -confined in sphereraw.fe\".",
